{{Year in Guinea|2007}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[2007]] in the [[Guinea|Republic of Guinea]]'''.

==Events==
===January===
* January 10 - A general strike starts in Guinea, with trade unions calling for pay rises, the return to jail of [[Mamadou Sylla]] and the resignation of President [[Lansana Conté]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6247965.stm | title=Guinea strike over sick president | date=10 January 2007 | accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>

===February===
* February 22 - President Lansana Conté appoints Lansana Kouyaté as the new Prime Minister of Guinea after reaching an agreement with the trade union movement and the Opposition.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6399235.stm | title=Guineans back to work after deal | date=27 February 2007 | accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>

===March===
* March 28 - Lansana Conté names a new government led by [[Lansana Kouyaté]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/6505263.stm | title=Guinea's leader names government | date=28 March 2007 | accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref>

