The '''Custodial Institutions Agency'''<ref>"[http://www.dji.nl/Images/Brochure%20Custodial%20Institutions%20Agency_tcm93-256648.pdf Custodial Institutions Agency Where freedom ends and may be regained]." Custodial Institutions Agency. Retrieved on 18 February 2011.</ref> ({{lang-nl|'''Dienst Justitiële Inrichtingen'''}}, "Department of Correctional Institutions," '''DJI''') is responsible for the [[criminal justice system of the Netherlands|incarceration]] of adults in the Netherlands. It is subordinate to the [[Ministry of Public Safety and Justice (Netherlands)|Ministry of Public Safety and Justice]]. The agency has its headquarters in [[The Hague]].<ref>"[http://www.dji.nl/Organisatie/Locaties/index.aspx Adressen en meer informatie locaties DJI]." Custodial Institutions Agency. Retrieved on 18 February 2011. "Hoofdkantoor DJI Postadres Postbus 30132 2500 GC DEN HAAG Bezoekadres Schedeldoekshaven 101 2511 EM DEN HAAG"</ref>

The agency's sole institution in the [[Caribbean Netherlands]] is the [[JI Caribisch Nederland]] in [[Kralendijk]], [[Bonaire]].<ref>"[http://www.dji.nl/Organisatie/Locaties/Caribisch-Nederland/ JI Caribisch Nederland]."</ref>

