'''Leo Pokrowsky''' (died 25 December 1900 in [[Utrecht, KwaZulu-Natal|Utrecht]], [[Kwazulu Natal]], [[South Africa]]) was a [[Poland|Pole]] and Captain in the Russian Army, who fought and died on the side of the [[Boers]] during the [[Second Anglo-Boer War]].  He was killed on Christmas Day 1900 when he and his men attacked the British garrison in Utrecht.

A commemorative plaque to his memory can be seen on the Burgher monument in the town of [[Utrecht, KwaZulu-Natal|Utrecht]].

