{{refimprove|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Estonia}} "Let's Get Loud" | image = | caption = | year = 2005 | country = Estonia | artist = [[Suntribe]] | as = | with = | language = English | languages = | composer = [[Sven Lõhmus]] | lyricist = [[Sven Lõhmus]] | conductor = | place = | points = | place_semi = 20th | points_semi = 31 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?2005ee English] | clip = | prev = Tii | prev_link = Tii | next = Through My Window | next_link = Through My Window }} "'''Let's Get Loud'''" was the [[Estonia]]n entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005]], performed in English by [[Suntribe]]. The author of the music and lyrics was [[Sven Lõhmus]].
As Estonia had not qualified for the final in their previous appearance, the song was performed in the semi-final. Here, it was performed twelfth (following Belgium's [[Nuno Resende]] with "[[Le grand soir (song)|Le grand soir]]" and preceding Norway's [[Wig Wam]] with "[[In My Dreams (Wig Wam song)|In My Dreams]]"). At the close of voting, it had received 31 points, placing 20th in a field of 25 songs<ref>{{cite web|title=Eurovision Song Contest 2005 Semi-Final|url=http://www.eurovision.tv/page/history/by-year/contest?event=157|website=Eurovision Song Contest|publisher=European Broadcasting Union|accessdate=22 August 2015}}</ref> and failing to qualify for the final - additionally, forcing Estonia to enter the Contest at the semi-final stage at their next appearance.
[[Suntribe]] was put on by the composer [[Sven Lõhmus]] just for the occasion, the follow-up single months after the Eurovision failed short to enter the charts. The band consisted of [[Mari-Leen Kaselaan]], [[Janika Vilipo]], [[Rebecca Kontus]], [[Laura Põldvere]] and [[Daana Ots]].
It was succeeded as [[Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest|Estonian representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006 Contest]] by [[Sandra Oxenryd]] with "[[Through My Window]]".
