ar-tailed godwit]]''' |[[File:BartailedGodwit24.jpg|100px]] |''Limosa lapponica'' |[[Scolopacidae]] |6,000 metres (20,000 feet)<ref name="Whiteman"/><ref name="Elphick">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j91I9I4pq20C&pg=PT28 |title = The Atlas of Bird Migration: Tracing the Great Journeys of the World's Birds | first = Jonathan | last = Elphick | publisher = Struik | year = 2007 | isbn = 1770074996 | page = 23}}</ref> |It can reach this height while migrating. |- |'''[[White stork]]''' |[[File:Ciconia ciconia - 01.jpg|100px]] |''Ciconia ciconia'' |[[Ciconiidae]] |4,800 metres (16,000 feet).<ref name="Elphick"/> |It can reach this height while migrating. |}
